==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whitening
<hw>Whit"en*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act or process of making or becoming white.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is used to render white; whiting.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Whitening stone</b></col>, <cd>a sharpening and polishing
stone used by cutlers; also, a finishing grindstone of fine
texture.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>White person</ent>⟦br⟧
